UNITED STATES of America v. HYMAN MICHAELS COMPANY. No. 6073. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Nov. 4, 1936.

Before EVANS, SPARKS, and AL-SCHULER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On petition of counsel for appellant; it is now here ordered and adjudged that this cause be docketed in this court and that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed.
